# npm-bundled transitive dependencies (minimatch, tar)
# These are internal to npm's own node_modules and only used during
# package installation, not at application runtime. They will be fixed
# when Node.js ships a release with updated npm.

# minimatch: DoS via crafted glob patterns (npm-internal)
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# tar: file overwrite via malicious archive (npm-internal)
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802

# Ubuntu base-image findings. These are in packages shipped by the
# ubuntu:24.04 base image (pinned by SHA in docker/Dockerfile.base) and
# get refreshed when the base image is rebuilt by the
# `Docker Base Image` workflow. Listing them here keeps the per-PR
# Trivy scan green between base-image rebuilds.

